---
import ArticleLayout from '../../layouts/ArticleLayout.astro';
import { localizedPath } from '../../i18n/utils';

const locale = 'en';
---

<ArticleLayout
  title="Terms of Use"
  description="The terms that apply to using WorthCalc's free browser-based money calculators."
  locale={locale}
  updated="2026-07-03"
>
  <p>
    These Terms of Use govern your use of WorthCalc. By using this site, you
    agree to use the calculators responsibly, for lawful purposes, and to
    accept the limitations described below.
  </p>

  <h2>What WorthCalc is</h2>
  <p>
    WorthCalc provides free, browser-based calculators for common
    money-decision questions, such as whether an installment plan, a
    membership, a vehicle purchase, or a rent-versus-buy scenario is
    financially worthwhile at the numbers you provide. The calculators are
    general-purpose tools, not tailored advice for your specific situation.
  </p>

  <h2>Use at your own risk</h2>
  <p>
    Calculators and content on this site are provided for general convenience
    and educational purposes. Results depend entirely on the numbers you
    enter and the simplified assumptions each calculator documents on its
    page. You are responsible for reviewing the assumptions and results
    before relying on them for any real decision. See our
    <a href={localizedPath(locale, '/disclaimer')}>Disclaimer</a> for more on
    how to treat calculator output.
  </p>

  <h2>No warranty</h2>
  <p>
    WorthCalc is provided "as is" and "as available," without warranties of
